Package: natl
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Natural language to Linux shell commands
 Translates natural language into a single Linux shell command using
 a local LLM (Ollama). The command is printed to stdout so it can be
 inserted into the prompt without running it (e.g. via Ctrl+G in bash).
 .
 Requires Ollama running locally. Supports configuration menu when
 run with no arguments; config is stored in ~/.config/natl/config.json.
